<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ol>
      <li><m>\frac{3}{6}, \frac{1}{2}</m></li>
      <li><p>Sample response: Each 1 whole is partitioned into fourths. Five fourths are shaded, which represents <m>\frac{5}{4}</m>. Each fourth can be split into two equal parts, which makes 8 eighths in 1 whole. Ten eighths are shaded, so that’s <m>\frac{10}{8}</m>. </p> <p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Diagram." role="image" src="../../../../../../figures/tikz-file-158712.svg"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Expand image" src="../../../../../assets/expand-9ef5655e2d1b5ba286de1390c97f4243f15e264c89106027f5d071073ab562bb.png" title="Expand image"/><p>[@@@@@@@@] WARNING: Fix Image.</p><img alt="Diagram." role="image" src="../../../../../../figures/tikz-file-158712.svg" width="80%"/></li>
    </ol>
  </solution>


